{"type":"message","id":"b2a1f861","parentId":"14b558ec","timestamp":"2026-04-06T10:29:16.901Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the issue clearly:\n\n1. Last successful run: Sunday, April 5, 2026 at 5:58 AM (duration: 178 seconds, about 3 minutes)\n2. This morning's run (Monday, April 6): **TIMED OUT** after 63,894ms (~64 seconds) with the error \"Request timed out before a response was generated. Please try again, or increase `agents.defaults.timeoutSeconds` in your config.\"\n\nThe current timeout is 600 seconds (10 minutes), but the brief should only take ~3 minutes. So why did it time out after 64 seconds?\n\nWait - 63,894ms is about 64 seconds. But the timeout is set to 600 seconds. Something doesn't add up.\n\n\nActually, I need to clarify the timeout behavior. The `agents.defaults.timeoutSeconds` might be a hard limit on how long the LLM call itself can take, separate from the cron job timeout. So even though the cron is set for 600 seconds, if the underlying agent has a lower timeout configured, that would explain why it died at 64 seconds.\n\nBut looking at the timing data, the last successful run took 178 seconds while the failed one only ran for 64 seconds. This suggests the issue might be something environmental—maybe the network degraded, or OpenClaw was restarting, or the model was overloaded. I should increase the `agents.defaults.timeoutSeconds` as the error suggests, but first let me check what the current timeout is actually set to.","thinkingSignature":"6d2e973322bdac61c009121af0004486d4d1069d334090b85b915d8cc9c7c3ca"},{"type":"text","text":"Found it. The morning brief timed out at **64 seconds** — error says to increase `agents.defaults.timeoutSeconds`.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1zq0rz7qcjy7_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw config get agents.defaults.timeoutSeconds 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage"