{"type":"message","id":"2f22a4db","parentId":"d759c157","timestamp":"2026-04-06T10:29:27.623Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `agents.defaults.timeoutSeconds` is already 1200 (20 minutes). But the cron job timed out after 64 seconds. Let me check what the cron job timeout is set to - earlier we saw it's 600 seconds.\n\nWait, the error message says \"Request timed out before a response was generated. Please try again, or increase `agents.defaults.timeoutSeconds` in your config.\" This might be the isolated session timeout, not the LLM timeout.\n\nLet me check the session timeout settings. Actually, looking at the cron job config - it uses `isolated` session. Maybe the isolated session has a different timeout.\n\nLet me check the cron job's payload.timeoutSeconds - we saw it's 600. \n\nSo the 64-second timeout suggests the isolated session itself is hitting a limit before the cron job's 600-second timeout kicks in. The cron job config shows `sessionTarget: \"isolated\"` and `timeoutSeconds: 600`, but I need to trace through what the actual session timeout configuration is for isolated sessions.\n\nThe brief was successful on April 5, so something changed between then and now. Let me just increase the cron job timeout to 1200 to match what the agent is using, or try running it manually to see what the actual error is.","thinkingSignature":"41ca14f737baa81e9005cef03853dbe86da5427871f1889625309998a42545e9"},{"type":"text","text":"Timeout is 600s on the cron, agents.defaults is 1200s. Brief runs fine in ~3 min normally. Something's blocking it.\n\nLet me run it manually right now to see the actual error:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qtdtcp5iocgn_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw cron run 539a35f3-d9a1-412d-bbaa-b8c6c81feab2 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":21280,"output":365,"cacheRead":26978,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48623,"