{"type":"message","id":"268bd5f4","parentId":"c94d7487","timestamp":"2026-04-06T10:32:29.257Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Both the automatic run and the manual run timed out. The error is \"Request timed out before a response was generated.\" This means the model call itself is timing out, not the cron job or the isolated session.\n\nLet me check what the isolated session timeout is. The cron job uses `sessionTarget: \"isolated\"` with `payload.kind: \"agentTurn\"`. For isolated sessions, there might be a separate timeout.\n\nWait - the error says \"increase `agents.defaults.timeoutSeconds`\" but it's already 1200. However, the cron job has its own timeout setting in `payload.timeoutSeconds`. Let me check the full cron job config again.\n\nActually, looking at the cron job config output from earlier:\n\n\nThe cron job has `timeoutSeconds: 600` which should be plenty since the morning brief only needs ~180 seconds. But both runs timed out - the first after 64 seconds and the second after 110 seconds. The brief uses a skill file that sends messages one at a time, so each message needs to complete before the next one starts.\n\nLooking at the output tokens from the second run (837 tokens), the model is generating responses but then hitting a timeout before it can actually send the messages via Telegram. The model is responding fine, but something about the message sending is causing the delay. might be slow.\n\nLet me think about what could cause this:\n1. The skill has a Python script for weather - maybe that's hanging\n2. The email check might be hanging\n3. The calendar check might be hanging\n4. The Bible verse fetch might be hanging\n\nSince the brief sends one section at a time and waits for each to complete, any one section hanging could cause the whole thing to timeout.\n\nBut wait - the brief is SUPPOSED to send one section at a time. The skill instructions say to send each section as its own Telegram message. If the model is timing out between messages, that means the isolated session itself is timing out, not the LLM call.\n\nSo the issue is likely:\n1. The isolated session has a hard timeout (maybe 120 seconds?)\n2. The skill takes ~3 minutes total but the session times out after some shorter period\n3. I need to either speed up the brief or increase the session timeout\n\nLet me increase the cron job timeout from 600 to 1800 seconds (30 minutes) to give it more time.","thinkingSignature":"ec07564eb325bc98a2c193c2b090a1d6e90743eb9bb1db1a7c155acfb0efa02a"},{"type":"text","text":"Both runs timed out — the model is responding (837 tokens output) but something in the skill is hanging between sections.\n\nLet me check what happens when I run the skill directly:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_u9svttrq1lq7_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 ~/.openclaw/skills/morning-brief/weather_script.py 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":23802,"output":569,"cacheRead":26978,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":51349,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775471534811,"responseId":"0622beae9705fde7495e7654a2426a0b"}}
