{"type":"message","id":"36b693cc","parentId":"8a32d122","timestamp":"2026-04-06T10:33:50.355Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me update the Gmail section of the morning brief skill to use gog instead of the broken script. Let me first read the full SKILL.md to see the Gmail section.","thinkingSignature":"d57753f125e771c1ee0db4f442eb418bb9b1949a5dc61ad5a0e64643de0a3101"},{"type":"text","text":"Now update the Gmail part to use gog:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_c3eygcbgxw55_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/skills/morning-brief/SKILL.md","offset":1,"limit":200}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":30041,"output":111,"cacheRead":26978,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57130,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775471626043,"responseId":"0622bf0a53843ed9d18d148dd102547a"}}
{"type":"message","id":"88c5a776","parentId":"36b693cc","timestamp":"2026-04-06T10:33:50.698Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_c3eygcbgxw55_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Morning Brief Skill\n\nA daily morning brief delivered to Bobby at 5:30 AM via Telegram.\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nEvery morning at 5:30 AM, run this skill to compile a comprehensive morning brief. The brief keeps Bobby informed about weather, news, his schedule, and relevant content.\n\n**Delivery:** Telegram (EACH SECTION AS SEPARATE MESSAGE)  \n**Time:** 5:30 AM daily  \n**Location:** Knoxville, TN (37919)\n\n---\n\n## ⚠️ CRITICAL: ONE SECTION AT A TIME\n\nComplete and send EACH section as its OWN Telegram message, ONE AT A TIME. Do not run all sections together.\n\nProcess:\n1. Complete Section 1 (Header), SEND the message\n2. Then work on Section 2 (Weather), SEND the message\n3. Then work on Section 3 (Bible Verse), SEND the message\n4. ... and so on\n\nThis prevents timeout issues and allows you to verify each section before moving on.\n\nOrder:\n1. Header → Message 1\n2. Weather → Message 2\n3. Bible Verse → Message 3\n4. Emails → Message 4\n5. Calendar → Message 5\n6. Reminders → Message 6\n7. Suggestions → Message 7\n\n---\n\n## Sections (In Order)\n\n### 1. Header\n\n**Format:**\n```\nGood morning, Bobby! ☀️\n\n[Day], [Month Date], [Year]\n\nHere's what we've got going on for today…\n```\n\n**Example:**\n```\nGood morning, Bobby! ☀️\n\nTuesday, March 10, 2026\n\nHere's what we've got going on for today…\n```\n\n**Notes:**\n- Emoji can vary (☀️, 🌞, 🍳, etc.)\n- Can switch up the phrasing slightly each day but keep the same vibe\n- Date format: \"Tuesday, March 10, 2026\" (or \"March 10, 2026\")\n\n---\n\n### 2. Weather (Knoxville)\n\n**Source:** Python script using wttr.in JSON API (avoids browser rendering bugs)\n\n**Command:**\n```bash\npython3 ~/.openclaw/skills/morning-brief/weather_script.py\n```\n\n**Expected output format:**\n```\n🌤️ Knoxville Weather — [Date]\n\nNOW: [temp]° (feels like [feels]°)\nHIGH: [high]° | LOW: [low]°\nWIND: [wind] | HUMIDITY: [humidity]% | UV: [uv#] ([uv-level]) | RAIN: [rain]%\n\n⏰ HOUR BY HOUR:\n9AM: [temp]° [emoji]\n12PM: [temp]° [emoji]\n3PM: [temp]° [emoji]\n6PM: [temp]° [emoji]\n9PM: [temp]° [emoji]\n\n💡 VERDICT: [One sentence advice based on weather]\n```\n\n**Notes:**\n- The script outputs the weather in the correct format above\n- Add YOUR SCHEDULE and WEATHER-AFFECTED REMINDERS sections after the script output\n- Only show reminders that could be affected by weather (outdoor activities, travel, etc.)\n- Link weather to schedule when relevant\n\n---\n\n### 3. Bible Verse of the Day\n\n**Source:** verseoftheday.com (via OpenClaw browser)\n\n**Command:**\n```bash\nopenclaw browser open \"https://www.verseoftheday.com\"\nopenclaw browser snapshot\n```\n\nExtract the verse and reference from the snapshot.\n```\n📖 BIBLE VERSE OF DAY\n\n\"[verse_text]\"\n— [reference]\n\n💡 TODAY'S MOTIVATION: [2-3 sentences personalizing this verse to Bobby's day. \n**CRITICAL:** You MUST reference:\n- His calendar events for today/tomorrow\n- His reminders \n- Projects or things he's told you about recently\n- Any bills, deadlines, or upcoming events\n\nMake it motivational, personal, and real. Be specific!]\n```\n\n**Example:**\n```\n📖 BIBLE VERSE OF THE DAY\n\n\"God is our refuge and strength, an ever-present help in trouble.\"\n— Psalm 46:1 (NIV)\n\n💡 TODAY'S MOTIVATION: You've got Logan, a solid setup with OpenClaw, and a good vibe going. When things get crazy (and they will), remember — you've got strength around you. Lean on what you've built.\n```\n\n**Example 2 (busy day):**\n```\n📖 BIBLE VERSE OF THE DAY\n\n\"The Lord is my shepherd; I shall not want.\"\n— Psalm 23:1 (NIV)\n\n💡 TODAY'S MOTIVATION: You've got a full day ahead. Between work, Logan, and all your projects, remember — you don't need to chase everything. You've got what you need. Focus on the priorities.\n```\n\n**Notes:**\n- Always include the \"💡 TODAY'S MOTIVATION\" line\n- Make it PERSONAL — reference specific things from his day (calendar, reminders, projects)\n- Keep it 2-3 sentences, not too long\n- Make it motivational but grounded\n- Can vary the emoji too (✨💪🌟🙌)\n\n---\n\n### 4. Email Summary\n\n**Source:** Gmail API (NOT gog CLI - gog is limited to ~12 emails)\n\n**Account:** rtg.bobby@gmail.com\n\n**CRITICAL:** Use Python with Gmail API directly. gog CLI only shows ~12 emails and will miss most of your inbox!\n\n**Python Script:**\n```python\nimport json\nfrom google.oauth2.credentials import Credentials\nfrom google.auth.transport.requests import Request\nfrom googleapiclient.discovery import build\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta\n\nwith open('/Users/bobbygalletta/.config/gmail_oauth/credentials.json') as f:\n    data = json.load(f)\n    \ncreds = Credentials(\n    token=data['token'],\n    refresh_token=data['refresh_token'],\n    client_id=data['client_id'],\n    client_secret=data['client_secret'],\n    token_uri=data['token_uri'],\n)\n\nif creds.expired:\n    creds.refresh(Request())\n\nservice = build('gmail', 'v1', credentials=creds)\n\n# Get emails from yesterday AND today\nyesterday = (datetime.now() - timedelta(days=1)).strftime(\"%Y/%m/%d\")\nquery = f'in:inbox after:{yesterday}'\n\nres = service.users().messages().list(userId='me', q=query, maxResults=100).execute()\nmsgs = res.get('messages', [])\nprint(f'Total: {len(msgs)}')\n\nfor m in msgs:\n\n[260 more lines in file. Use offset=201 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775471630640}}
