{"type":"message","id":"4f2ee454","parentId":"fa660038","timestamp":"2026-04-06T10:35:08.529Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No upcoming events in Family Calendar this week. That's fine - the script works, there just aren't any events.\n\nNow let me focus on the real issue - the Gmail auth. Let me try to fix it by using gog's token store. Actually, the cleanest fix is to update the skill to use gog CLI instead of the broken Gmail API script. GOG is authenticated and working.\n\nLet me update the SKILL.md to use gog for Gmail. Let me also increase the cron timeout to be safe.\n\nBut first, let me think about what's actually causing the timeout. The cron times out with \"Request timed out before a response was generated.\" This could mean:\n\n\nThe model is taking too long to generate a response because it's trying to call the Gmail API which hangs with bad credentials. The credential error should return quickly, but maybe there's a retry loop or the error handling is getting stuck somewhere. Let me test if the Gmail script actually times out or fails fast.","thinkingSignature":"e8e5c304360a10d2468f6ad93432e5e38fec0a8725585ceedb12b10af6c7f385"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_a40k5r1lfvcx_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"timeout 10 python3 ~/.openclaw/skills/morning-brief/gmail_script.py 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":33929,"output":244,"cacheRead":26978,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61151,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775471700376,"responseId":"0622bf54bc196c9699bd2be15210c36e"}}
