{"type":"message","id":"f753cb4d","parentId":"941ce93b","timestamp":"2026-04-06T10:35:30.727Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Gmail script fails fast (within 5 seconds) with an error, not a hang. So the timeout is not caused by the Gmail script hanging.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The morning brief skill has the model run through 7 sections. Each section involves:\n1. Running a script or command\n2. Formatting the output\n3. Sending a Telegram message\n\nThe timeout happens after 64-110 seconds. This is not enough time to run all 7 sections if each one involves multiple steps.\n\nThe key insight from the SKILL.md is: \"Complete and send EACH section as its OWN Telegram message, ONE AT A TIME.\"\n\nThis means the skill is designed to send message 1, then message 2, etc. \n\nBut when an isolated session runs the skill, it should stay alive between sections—yet it's timing out after 64-110 seconds. The successful run took ~3 minutes, so the isolated session must be getting killed prematurely. I think the issue is that the model generates a response for one section and sends it, but then when it tries to process the next section, the session has already timed out.\n\nLooking at the actual run data, the model only generated 837 tokens before timing out. At roughly 50 tokens per second for MiniMax, that's only about 16 seconds of actual generation time. The rest of the 64-110 seconds is the isolated session sitting idle waiting for the model to respond again. So the session timeout appears to be around 60-110 seconds of inactivity, not generation time.\n\nThe cron timeout is set to 600 seconds, but something else is causing the session to terminate after just 64-110 seconds of overall elapsed time. I should increase the cron timeout from 600 to 1200 seconds and also fix the Gmail script to use gog instead, which might help the sessions complete faster. But I'm also wondering if the real issue is that the isolated session itself has a hard timeout that's shorter than what the cron job allows.\n\nLooking at the OpenClaw documentation on isolated sessions, there's a `timeoutSeconds` setting that controls the agent turn timeout in isolated mode. I need to check the config to see what that value is currently set to.","thinkingSignature":"e1d362d4d431b5cddedf7676310c9ad15c19bbb2415f0868060844b9deb7c8b2"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2u0n8ctr34f9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw config get agents.defaults 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(json.dumps(d, indent=2))\" 2>/dev/null | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":34402,"output":526,"cacheRead":26978,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61906,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775471714829,"responseId":"0622bf6331d95b32c7a0a32d9dc864ab"}}
