{"type":"message","id":"540f31f2","parentId":"46d7db7c","timestamp":"2026-04-06T17:25:15.142Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_nca3d7a8y6fd_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"• [Sender] — [Subject line]\n...\n\n🎉 PROMOTIONS & NEWSLETTERS ([count])\n• [Sender] (x2) — Subject 1 / Subject 2\n...\n\n📨 FROM YOU ([count])\n• rtg.bobby@gmail.com — [Subject] (x2 if multiple)\n```\n\n**Categories to use:**\n- ⚠️ BILLS & PAYMENTS — money owed, charges, payments, invoices\n- 📬 PERSONAL/UPDATES — real notifications, updates to accounts, personal services\n- 💼 JOB SEARCH — hiring, applications, recruiter outreach\n- 🎵 MUSIC — music services, beats, audio platforms\n- 🎉 PROMOTIONS & NEWSLETTERS — sales, marketing, newsletters, promotional emails\n- 📨 FROM YOU — emails sent to yourself (test emails, notes, etc.)\n\n**Notes:**\n- Show ALL emails, no max limit\n- Group by sender within categories\n- Use (x2), (x3) notation for multiple emails from same sender\n- Sort categories by importance (bills first)\n\n---\n\n### 5. Calendar (7 Days)\n\n**Source:** icalbuddy (command-line calendar tool)\n\n**Command:**\n```bash\nicalbuddy -c \"Family Calendar\" eventsToday+7\n```\n\n**Format:** Just show the 7 days with any events. Keep it simple!\n\n**Important:** Use icalbuddy, NOT AppleScript. AppleScript is too slow and times out.\n\n**Command:**\n```bash\nosascript -e 'tell application \"Calendar\"\n tell calendar \"Family Calendar\"\n   set upcomingEvents to events whose start date > (current date - 86400) and start date < (current date + 86400 * 7)\n   repeat with evt in upcomingEvents\n     set evtSummary to summary of evt\n     set evtStart to start date of evt\n     set isAllDay to all-day event of evt\n     if isAllDay is true then\n       log evtSummary & \" | ALL-DAY\"\n     else\n       log evtSummary & \" | \" & (evtStart as string)\n     end if\n   end repeat\n end tell\nend tell'\n```\n\nIf no events show up, check for recurring events and calculate their next occurrence!\n\n**Format:**\n```\n📅 YOUR WEEK ([date] — [date])\n\nTUE 3/10:\n• [Event name] — 2:00 PM\nOR: \"• Free day!\"\n\nWED 3/11:\n• [Event name] — 6:00 PM\n\n...\n\n---\n\n💡 BASED ON YOUR SCHEDULE:\n\n• [Suggest something helpful based on what's on the calendar]\n• [If Logan has something, ask if he needs help preparing]\n• [If it's a free day, suggest something fun]\n```\n\n**Example:**\n```\n📅 YOUR WEEK (Mar 10 — Mar 16)\n\nTUE 3/10:\n• Free day!\n\nWED 3/11:\n• Team meeting — 2:00 PM\n\nTHU 3/12:\n• Dinner with Logan — 6:00 PM\n\nFRI 3/13:\n• No events\n\nSAT 3/14:\n\n[124 more lines in file. Use offset=300 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775496315035}}
