{"type":"message","id":"619ff2e3","parentId":"d75936f7","timestamp":"2026-04-06T17:25:22.204Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_awd6gci3281j_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"• No events\n\nSUN 3/15:\n• No events\n\nMON 3/16:\n• No events\n\n---\n\n💡 BASED ON YOUR SCHEDULE:\n\n• Wednesday has a meeting at 2pm — want me to prepare anything?\n• Thursday dinner with Logan — reservations set?\n• Free week otherwise! Any projects you want to work on?\n```\n\n**Notes:**\n- ALWAYS show 7 days out from today\n- Use short day format: TUE, WED, THU, FRI, SAT, SUN, MON\n- Show date: 3/10, 3/11, etc.\n- Include time if available\n- \"Free day!\" when no events\n- 💡 Suggestions at the bottom: make them helpful and relevant to what's on the calendar\n\n---\n\n### 6. Reminders\n\n**Source:** Apple Reminders via remindctl\n\n**Command:**\n```bash\nremindctl list Reminders\n```\n\n**Filter:** Show only incomplete reminders (items with [ ])\n\n**Format:**\n```\n📝 REMINDERS\n\n• [Reminder title]\n• [Reminder title]\nOR: \"None for today\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. Suggestions (How I Can Help Today)\n\n**Goal:** Suggest concrete ways Dean can actively help Bobby today by taking work off his plate, reducing decision fatigue, or preparing something useful for him.\n\n**Rules:**\n- Do NOT give generic life advice\n- Suggestions must be things Dean can help do, check, organize, draft, prep, or troubleshoot\n- Prioritize urgent, time-sensitive, money-related, schedule-related, or stress-reducing help first\n- If there is one clearly important task today, make that suggestion #1\n\n```\n**Tips:**\n- Keep it simple and actionable\n- Reference things from the brief (DoorDash order, calendar events, bills, reminders)\n- Focus on what Dean can DO for Bobby today, not just what Bobby should do\n- Tie suggestions to real items from the brief whenever possible\n- Good examples: checking important emails, turning reminders into a plan, helping with bills/payments, prepping content tasks, troubleshooting OpenClaw/tech, making a grocery/errand game plan\n- Keep suggestions specific enough that Bobby could immediately ask Dean to handle one\n\n**Format:**\n```\n💡 WAYS I CAN HELP TODAY\n\n1. [Actionable suggestion - specific thing Dean can do]\n2. [Another actionable suggestion]\n3. [Third actionable suggestion]\n4. [Fourth actionable suggestion]\n5. [Fifth actionable suggestion]\n6. [Sixth actionable suggestion]\n7. [Seventh actionable suggestion]\n\n---\n\n## Quality Checklist\n\nBefore sending, verify:\n- [ ] All 10 messages sent (8 sections + X split into 3)\n- [ ] Each section sent as SEPARATE Telegram message\n- [ ] Weather shows actual temp, feels like, wind\n- [ ] Bible verse is current + personalized motivation\n- [ ] Emails: show 10 per category, ALL bills\n- [ ] Calendar shows 7 days + recurring bills\n- [ ] X: 5 For You, 5 Following, 5 Trending (15 total)\n- [ ] Each X post has: handle, preview, Why (1-2 sentences), [view] link\n- [ ] Suggestions are actionable (things Dean can DO for Bobby)\n\n---\n\n## ⚡ FEEDBACK LOOP — ALWAYS BE REFINING\n\nAfter sending the brief:\n\n[24 more lines in file. Use offset=400 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775496322106}}
{"type":"message","id":"8e506428","parentId":"619ff2e3","timestamp":"2026-04-06T17:25:32.804Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to update the Calendar section to include bills from the bills_april_2026.json file. Let me edit the SKILL.md to add a bills check to the Calendar section.","thinkingSignature":"c88170f0b362fa425885d6ca03c46ac98efd9b8b185f87458e5c8f1a038d9f12"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ia0pzwpti4ep_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/skills/morning-brief/SKILL.md","edits":[{"oldText":"### 5. Calendar (7 Days)\n\n**Source:** icalbuddy (command-line calendar tool)\n\n**Command:**\n```bash\nicalbuddy -c \"Family Calendar\" eventsToday+7\n```\n\n**Format:** Just show the 7 days with any events. Keep it simple!\n\n**Important:** Use icalbuddy, NOT AppleScript. AppleScript is too slow and times out.\n\n**Command:**\n```bash\nosascript -e 'tell application \"Calendar\"\n tell calendar \"Family Calendar\"\n   set upcomingEvents to events whose start date > (current date - 86400) and start date < (current date + 86400 * 7)\n   repeat with evt in upcomingEvents\n     set evtSummary to summary of evt\n     set evtStart to start date of evt\n     set isAllDay to all-day event of evt\n     if isAllDay is true then\n       log evtSummary & \" | ALL-DAY\"\n     else\n       log evtSummary & \" | \" & (evtStart as string)\n     end if\n   end repeat\n end tell\nend tell'\n```","newText":"### 5. Calendar (7 Days) + Bills\n\n**Source:** icalbuddy + bills JSON file\n\n**Calendar Command:**\n```bash\nicalbuddy -c \"Family Calendar\" eventsToday+7\n```\n\n**Bills Command:**\n```bash\npython3 -c \"\nimport json\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta\n\ntoday = datetime.now()\nweek_end = today + timedelta(days=7)\n\ntry:\n    with open('/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/data/bills_april_2026.json') as f:\n        bills = json.load(f)\n    \n    upcoming = []\n    for b in bills:\n        due = datetime.strptime(b['dueDate'], '%Y-%m-%d')\n        if today <= due <= week_end:\n            status = '✅ PAID' if b.get('paid') else '⚠️ DUE'\n            upcoming.append(f\\\"• {b['name']} — {b['dueDate'][5:]} — \\${b['amount']:.2f} [{status}]\\\")\n    \n    if upcoming:\n        print('\\n'.join(upcoming))\n    else:\n        print('No bills due this week')\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f'Could not load bills: {e}')\n\"\n```"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":67156,"output":657,"cacheRead":21957,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":89770,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775496322206,"responseId":"06231f82ba3db30de49d62b7aea42083"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9775f3ff","parentId":"8e506428","timestamp":"2026-04-06T17:25:33.065Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ia0pzwpti4ep_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in /Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/skills/morning-brief/SKILL.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 223 - Sort categories by importance (bills first)\n 224 \n 225 ---\n 226 \n-227 ### 5. Calendar (7 Days)\n+227 ### 5. Calendar (7 Days) + Bills\n 228 \n-229 **Source:** icalbuddy (command-line calendar tool)\n+229 **Source:** icalbuddy + bills JSON file\n 230 \n-231 **Command:**\n+231 **Calendar Command:**\n 232 ```bash\n 233 icalbuddy -c \"Family Calendar\" eventsToday+7\n 234 ```\n 235 \n-236 **Format:** Just show the 7 days with any events. Keep it simple!\n+236 **Bills Command:**\n+237 ```bash\n+238 python3 -c \"\n+239 import json\n+240 from datetime import datetime, timedelta\n 237 \n-238 **Important:** Use icalbuddy, NOT AppleScript. AppleScript is too slow and times out.\n+242 today = datetime.now()\n+243 week_end = today + timedelta(days=7)\n 239 \n-240 **Command:**\n-241 ```bash\n-242 osascript -e 'tell application \"Calendar\"\n-243  tell calendar \"Family Calendar\"\n-244    set upcomingEvents to events whose start date > (current date - 86400) and start date < (current date + 86400 * 7)\n-245    repeat with evt in upcomingEvents\n-246      set evtSummary to summary of evt\n-247      set evtStart to start date of evt\n-248      set isAllDay to all-day event of evt\n-249      if isAllDay is true then\n-250        log evtSummary & \" | ALL-DAY\"\n-251      else\n-252        log evtSummary & \" | \" & (evtStart as string)\n-253      end if\n-254    end repeat\n-255  end tell\n-256 end tell'\n+245 try:\n+246     with open('/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/data/bills_april_2026.json') as f:\n+247         bills = json.load(f)\n+248     \n+249     upcoming = []\n+250     for b in bills:\n+251         due = datetime.strptime(b['dueDate'], '%Y-%m-%d')\n+252         if today <= due <= week_end:\n+253             status = '✅ PAID' if b.get('paid') else '⚠️ DUE'\n+254             upcoming.append(f\\\"• {b['name']} — {b['dueDate'][5:]} — \\${b['amount']:.2f} [{status}]\\\")\n+255     \n+256     if upcoming:\n+257         print('\\n'.join(upcoming))\n+258     else:\n+259         print('No bills due this week')\n+260 except Exception as e:\n+261     print(f'Could not load bills: {e}')\n+262 \"\n 257 ```\n 258 \n 259 If no events show up, check for recurring events and calculate their next occurrence!\n 260 \n     ...","firstChangedLine":227},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775496332969}}
{"type":"message","id":"f5b0729a","parentId":"9775f3ff","timestamp":"2026-04-06T17:25:48.295Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to update the Calendar format section to include bills in the display. Let me also update the format example to show bills.","thinkingSignature":"b8cf199f1d12a09d601cfd57d12b695b5eb2f9aaee7ef7192072d1cdf44a1d17"},{"type":"text","text":"Now update the Calendar format to show bills inline:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6wi3a75w49v7_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/skills/morning-brief/SKILL.md","edits":[{"oldText":"**Format:**\n```\n📅 YOUR WEEK ([date] — [date])\n\nTUE 3/10:\n• [Event name] — 2:00 PM\nOR: \"• Free day!\"\n\nWED 3/11:\n• [Event name] — 6:00 PM\n\n...\n\n---\n\n💡 BASED ON YOUR SCHEDULE:\n\n• [Suggest something helpful based on what's on the calendar]\n• [If Logan has something, ask if he needs help preparing]\n• [If it's a free day, suggest something fun]\n```\n\n**Example:**\n```\n📅 YOUR WEEK (Mar 10 — Mar 16)\n\nTUE 3/10:\n• Free day!\n\nWED 3/11:\n• Team meeting — 2:00 PM\n\nTHU 3/12:\n• Dinner with Logan — 6:00 PM\n\nFRI 3/13:\n• No events\n\nSAT 3/14:\n• No events\n\nSUN 3/15:\n• No events\n\nMON 3/16:\n• No events\n\n---\n\n💡 BASED ON YOUR SCHEDULE:\n\n• Wednesday has a meeting at 2pm — want me to prepare anything?\n• Thursday dinner with Logan — reservations set?\n• Free week otherwise! Any projects you want to work on?\n```\n\n**Notes:**\n- ALWAYS show 7 days out from today\n- Use short day format: TUE, WED, THU, FRI, SAT, SUN, MON\n- Show date: 3/10, 3/11, etc.\n- Include time if available\n- \"Free day!\" when no events\n- 💡 Suggestions at the bottom: make them helpful and relevant to what's on the calendar","newText":"**Format:**\n```\n📅 YOUR WEEK ([date] — [date])\n\nTUE 3/10:\n• [Event name] — 2:00 PM\n• ⚠️ Bills: [list any bills due]\nOR: \"• Free day!\"\n\nWED 3/11:\n• [Event name] — 6:00 PM\n• ⚠️ Bills: [list any bills due]\n\n...\n\n---\n\n💡 BASED ON YOUR SCHEDULE:\n\n• [Suggest something helpful based on what's on the calendar]\n• [Bill reminder: e.g., \"T-Mobile due Friday - \\$98.30\"]\n• [If it's a free day, suggest something fun]\n```\n\n**Example:**\n```\n📅 YOUR WEEK (Apr 6 — Apr 12)\n\nMON 4/6:\n• Free day!\n• ⚠️ Bills: KUB (old apartment) — 4/3 — $362.20\n\nTUE 4/7:\n• Free day!\n• ⚠️ Bills: T-Mobile (2 of 2) — 4/8 — $98.30\n\nWED 4/8:\n• Free day!\n\nTHU 4/9:\n• Free day!\n• ⚠️ Bills: Affirm Hilton Hotels — 4/9 — $23.50\n\nFRI 4/10:\n• Pay T-Mobile (Family Calendar)\n• ⚠️ Bills: Affirm Virtual Card — 4/11 — $25.74\n\nSAT 4/11:\n• Free day!\n\nSUN 4/12:\n• Orthodox Easter (US Holidays)\n• ⚠️ Bills: Affirm Virtual Card — 4/12 — $29.87\n\n---\n\n💡 BASED ON YOUR SCHEDULE:\n\n• Thursday: Affirm Hilton Hotels due ($23.50)\n• Friday: T-Mobile on the calendar + another Affirm payment\n• Sunday: Orthodox Easter with Logan — any plans?\n• KUB (old apartment) $362.20 is marked \"not urgent\" — confirm if it needs attention\n```\n\n**Notes:**\n- ALWAYS show 7 days out from today\n- Use short day format: TUE, WED, THU, FRI, SAT, SUN, MON\n- Show date: 3/10, 3/11, etc.\n- Include time if available\n- \"Free day!\" when no events\n- ALWAYS check bills_april_2026.json for upcoming bills this week\n- Flag unpaid bills with ⚠️ and their due date\n- 💡 Suggestions at the bottom: make them helpful and relevant to what's on the calendar"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":67856,"output":1120,"cacheRead":21957,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":90933,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775496333067,"responseId":"06231f8d5fd1a29f1453837bcb26fce2"}}
