{"type":"message","id":"0f97d3b3","parentId":"c53fb3af","timestamp":"2026-04-07T00:17:47.153Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the actual issue is:\n- Battery Monitor: set to `local-tiny` — this is the problem\n- All others: set to `MiniMax-M2.7` with 1200s timeout — these should be fine\n\nBut Bobby said they're all erroring. Let me check the cron runs for each to see what's happening. Actually, the issue might be that some of these crons are using `isolated` session type with no model override, but the session type might be the problem.\n\nActually wait — the cron list output earlier showed:\n- `d69fb9e2... Battery Monitor` — model: local-tiny (THIS IS WRONG)\n\n\n- Other crons with \"error\" status — let me check their most recent run to see what's actually failing.","thinkingSignature":"edeffe6df0fb9a1abf280224ca82991f4ba6d5000e6bbda1d2495bcd2bd18f6f"},{"type":"text","text":"Battery Monitor is the only one with wrong model (`local-tiny`). The others are set to `MiniMax-M2.7` but still erroring. Let me check their recent failures:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0rb6pc4webpi_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw cron runs --id 7ea307af-cd86-49f7-9975-723670e3b304 2>&1 | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":73083,"output":262,"cacheRead":21957,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":95302,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775521059734,"responseId":"062380232f20d777b502fa10c366660c"}}
