{"type":"message","id":"ae18fe01","parentId":"fd73d9e6","timestamp":"2026-04-07T00:18:09.664Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"These are all timing out after ~74-86 seconds. The error says \"increase `agents.defaults.timeoutSeconds`\" but we already have that set to 1200. The issue is the cron job payload has a shorter timeout.\n\nLet me check what timeout the cron job itself is using. The cron job payload timeout overrides the global `agents.defaults.timeoutSeconds`. Let me look at the full cron job payload.\n\nActually wait — I updated the morning brief cron from 600s to 1800s earlier. Let me check the current timeout on the errored crons. The model is set correctly to MiniMax-M2.7, so the issue must be the timeoutSeconds in the cron payload.","thinkingSignature":"cf93f164758e0f32fb385d04388c468bfc0d0dc5fb87cfb4f88128fec1a867df"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_o8frrh84v4ek_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw cron list --json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\ndata = json.load(sys.stdin)\nfor job in data.get('jobs', []):\n    if job.get('id') in ['7ea307af-cd86-49f7-9975-723670e3b304', '4ad06060-6fbc-4762-80e4-9dcdb6ac7a0d', '487e71b7-8898-4da8-8e53-5237c045750c', '9865c737-e428-4480-bd2e-3420944dc2b5', '7b25e1f1-42f6-4fde-8d49-fa3c608899d7']:\n        print(f\\\"{job['name']}: model={job.get('payload',{}).get('model','?')} timeout={job.get('payload',{}).get('timeoutSeconds','?')}\\\")\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":73943,"output":387,"cacheRead":21957,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":96287,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775521081451,"responseId":"06238039e44639a80543e0b27cf95bbf"}}
